video.title: Star Wars: The Clone Wars
video.synopsis: Follow the animated adventures of the Jedi knights, including Anakin Skywalker and his master, Obi-Wan Kenobi. Season 6 available only on Netflix.

episodes.synopsis: Jedi Master Yoda and three clone troopers must face off against Count Dooku's dreaded assassin Ventress and her massive droid army.
episodes.title: Ambush

episodes.synopsis: An attack by a devastating new Separatist weapon leaves Jedi Master Plo Koon and his clone troopers struggling to survive.
episodes.title: Rising Malevolence

episodes.synopsis: Anakin utilizes new long-range Y-wing bombers to lead a bold strike on Gen. Grievous's warship and its destructive weapon.
episodes.title: Shadow of Malevolence

episodes.synopsis: Padmé Amidala and C-3PO are taken hostage by Gen. Grievous, leaving Anakin and Obi-Wan to save the senator and finish off the Malevolence.
episodes.title: Destroy Malevolence

episodes.synopsis: Clone Officers Rex and Cody must inspire their rookie unit to believe in themselves as they fight off a Droid Commando invasion.
episodes.title: Rookies

episodes.synopsis: Anakin must find the missing R2-D2 before the Separatists discover the Jedi military secrets locked in his memory banks.
episodes.title: Downfall of a Droid

episodes.synopsis: Anakin, Ahsoka and replacement droid R3 embark on a rescue mission when they learn R2-D2 is being held at Gen. Grievous's secret enemy listening post.
episodes.title: Duel of the Droids

episodes.synopsis: Jar Jar Binks and C-3PO fight to save Padmé Amidala from doom at the hands of evil Viceroy Nute Gunray.
episodes.title: Bombad Jedi

episodes.synopsis: Ahsoka and Jedi Master Luminara escort captured Viceroy Nute Gunray to trial, unaware that Count Dooku has dispatched a deadly assassin.
episodes.title: Cloak of Darkness

episodes.synopsis: Gen. Grievous must prove himself worthy of the Separatists when Count Dooku leads Jedi Master Kit Fisto to Grievous's villainous enclave.
episodes.title: Lair of Grievous

episodes.synopsis: During their own attempt to kidnap Count Dooku, Anakin and Obi-Wan discover that the Sith Lord has already been captured by pirates.
episodes.title: Dooku Captured

episodes.synopsis: While negotiating Count Dooku's ransom, Anakin and Obi-Wan are taken prisoner. The Jedi and Sith form an unlikely alliance in a bid to escape.
episodes.title: The Gungan General

episodes.synopsis: When Anakin is gravely injured in battle, Jedi Gen. Aayla Secura must teach Ahsoka the Jedi philosophy of having no personal attachments.
episodes.title: Jedi Crash

episodes.synopsis: While the Jedi combat a new Separatist weapon, the pacifist Lurmen must decide whether they will lie down to the oppressive Separatists or fight.
episodes.title: Defenders of Peace

episodes.synopsis: While investigating the disappearance of a clone security force, Anakin and Obi-Wan get caught in the middle of an escalating conflict.
episodes.title: Trespass

episodes.synopsis: Anakin and Obi-Wan discover evidence of a traitor in their ranks while attempting to lead Republic forces to liberate the planet of Christophsi.
episodes.title: The Hidden Enemy

episodes.synopsis: Padmé and Jar Jar are captured while searching for a secret bio-weapons lab, sparking Anakin, Obi-Wan and Ahsoka to try to save their friends.
episodes.title: Blue Shadow Virus

episodes.synopsis: The fatal Blue Shadow Virus is released, infecting Ahsoka, Padmé and many others -- and giving Anakin and Obi-Wan just 48 hours to find the antidote.
episodes.title: Mystery of the Thousand Moons

episodes.synopsis: Ahsoka disobeys Anakin's orders and loses most of her squadron, prompting Anakin to help give his Padawan a lesson in respect for authority.
episodes.title: Storm Over Ryloth

episodes.synopsis: Obi-Wan and a small clone force enter an occupied town and discover that its residents are being used as a human shield.
episodes.title: Innocents of Ryloth

episodes.synopsis: With his forces stretched thin, Mace Windu must convince Twi'lek freedom fighter Cham Syndulla to help him save the capital city from destruction.
episodes.title: Liberty on Ryloth

episodes.synopsis: To free crime lord Ziro the Hutt, Bounty Hunters seize control of the Senate Building and take hostages, unaware that Anakin is still inside.
episodes.title: Hostage Crisis

episodes.synopsis: Cad Bane infiltrates the Jedi Temple and attempts to steal an ancient Jedi Holocron. It's up to Ahsoka, Anakin and Obi-Wan to stop the bounty hunter.
episodes.title: Holocron Heist

episodes.synopsis: Anakin and Ahsoka intercept Cad Bane's warship, hoping to recover the stolen Jedi Holocron. But the Jedi underestimate the bounty hunter's tactics.
episodes.title: Cargo of Doom

episodes.synopsis: Cad Bane is given a new destructive mission: kidnap Force-sensitive children from across the galaxy and bring them to Mustafar for Sith training.
episodes.title: Children of the Force

episodes.synopsis: At the Jedi Council's request, Padmé investigates a Separatist conspiracy in the Senate.
episodes.title: Senate Spy

episodes.synopsis: Anakin, Ahsoka and Ki-Adi-Mundi lead a landing party to destroy a droid factory on Geonosis. They must stop it before it becomes active.
episodes.title: Landing at Point Rain

episodes.synopsis: Luminara and Anakin act as decoys to divert new enemy super-tanks, while Padawans Barriss Offee and Ahsoka try to destroy a Separatist droid factory.
episodes.title: Weapons Factory

episodes.synopsis: When Luminara goes missing, Obi-Wan and Ki-Adi-Mundi lead a platoon of clones in search of her, which takes them to a mysterious lair.
episodes.title: Legacy of Terror

episodes.synopsis: When Geonosian brain worms take control of their supply ship, Ahsoka and Barriss must stop the vessel from unleashing a deadly plague upon the galaxy.
episodes.title: Brain Invaders

episodes.synopsis: Jedi Master Eeth Koth is taken hostage and tortured by General Grievous. Anakin, Obi-Wan and Adi Gallia devise a daring rescue plan.
episodes.title: Grievous Intrigue

episodes.synopsis: While searching for General Grievous on Saleucami, Rex and the Jedi meet a clone deserter.
episodes.title: The Deserter

episodes.synopsis: When a wily pickpocket steals Ahsoka's lightsaber, she enlists the help of an ancient Jedi to track down her weapon and reclaim her honor.
episodes.title: Lightsaber Lost

episodes.synopsis: While investigating rumors of conspiracy surrounding Duchess Satine of Mandalore, Obi-Wan uncovers the truth about the mysterious "Mandalore Plot."
episodes.title: The Mandalore Plot

episodes.synopsis: As the Jedi and their clones defend Duchess Satine from assassination attempts, Anakin discovers that Obi-Wan and the Duchess have a history together.
episodes.title: Voyage of Temptation

episodes.synopsis: On Coruscant, Duchess Satine is framed for the creation of the Death Watch, a Mandalorian rebel group.
episodes.title: Duchess of Mandalore

episodes.synopsis: When Senator Onaconda Farr dies under suspicious circumstances, Padmé sets out to find the person who took the life of her favorite "uncle."
episodes.title: Senate Murders

episodes.synopsis: Obi-Wan and Anakin must deliver troops to Christophsis against a Separatist stronghold. They encounter Separatist Commander Admiral Trench.
episodes.title: Cat and Mouse

episodes.synopsis: Anakin, Obi-Wan and Ahoska form an uneasy partnership with four bounty hunters to protect a spice farmer from Hondo Onaka and his band of pirates.
episodes.title: Bounty Hunters

episodes.synopsis: The Republic's new super-weapon awakens the fearsome Zillo Beast of Malastare. Now the Jedi have a new problem on their hands.
episodes.title: The Zillo Beast

episodes.synopsis: Republic forces bring the Zillo Beast back to Coruscant for study. When it escapes, the Jedi must make a difficult moral choice.
episodes.title: The Zillo Beast Strikes Back

episodes.synopsis: A young boy wages war against the Jedi Knights who left him orphaned, bitter and alone. He enlists the aid of ruthless and deadly bounty hunters.
episodes.title: Death Trap

episodes.synopsis: When Boba Fett and his band of bounty hunters lead Anakin and Mace into a deadly trap on Vanqor, it's up to R2-D2 to battle his way back to Coruscant.
episodes.title: R2 Come Home

episodes.synopsis: After combing the Coruscant underworld for Boba Fett, Plo Koon and Ahsoka set out to capture him and his fellow bounty hunters on Florrum.
episodes.title: Lethal Trackdown

episodes.synopsis: Five headstrong clone cadets -- Hevy, Cutup, Droidbait, Fives and Echo -- struggle to complete their training on the ocean planet of Kamino.
episodes.title: Clone Cadets

episodes.synopsis: When the Republic learns of an impending Separatist attack on Kamino, Anakin Skywalker and Obi-Wan Kenobi hurry to the planet's defense.
episodes.title: ARC Troopers

episodes.synopsis: Ryloth is under siege. Trapped on the surface, Jedi Master Di rallies the local forces with the help of rebel leader Cham Syndulla.
episodes.title: Supply Lines

episodes.synopsis: When Chairman Papanoida's family is kidnapped for ransom, Ahsoka must team up with Pantoran Senator Riyo Chuchi to aid in recovering his family.
episodes.title: Sphere of Influence

episodes.synopsis: On a diplomatic mission to Mandalore, Senator Padmé Amidala uncovers a sinister plot lurking beneath the pacifist planet's serene façade.
episodes.title: Corruption

episodes.synopsis: Much to her chagrin, Ahsoka Tano is assigned to teach a class at the cadet academy on Mandalore.
episodes.title: The Academy

episodes.synopsis: Tasked with protecting Senator Padmé Amidala during a political mission to Alderaan, Ahsoka is plagued by visions of the bounty hunter, Aurra Sing.
episodes.title: Assassin

episodes.synopsis: While shopping on Coruscant, C-3PO is abducted by bounty hunter Cad Bane. Soon, both C-3PO and R2-D2 are pawns in Bane's plan to free Ziro the Hutt.
episodes.title: Evil Plans

episodes.synopsis: After being freed from a Republic prison by bounty hunter Cad Bane, Ziro the Hutt finds himself wanted by the shadowy Hutt Council.
episodes.title: Hunt for Ziro

episodes.synopsis: While the Senate is tied up over budgets and bills, Padmé and Ahsoka travel in secret to Raxus to forge a peace agreement with the Separatists.
episodes.title: Heroes on Both Sides

episodes.synopsis: Padmé Amidala, Bail Organa and Onaconda Farr attempt to rally the Senate against a bill that would appropriate funds for millions of new clone troops.
episodes.title: Pursuit of Peace

episodes.synopsis: Troubled by Asajj Ventress's growing prowess with the Dark Side of the Force, Darth Sidious commands Count Dooku to eliminate her.
episodes.title: Nightsisters

episodes.synopsis: Count Dooku visits the Nightsisters, seeking to replace Asajj Ventress with a new, deadlier apprentice.
episodes.title: Monster

episodes.synopsis: Sent to track the mysterious figure behind the deaths of several Jedi, Anakin and Obi-Wan find themselves on the trail of the monstrous Savage Opress.
episodes.title: Witches of the Mist

episodes.synopsis: A mysterious force draws Anakin Skywalker, Obi-Wan Kenobi and Ahsoka Tano to the distant planet of Mortis, where Anakin learns of his destiny.
episodes.title: Overlords

episodes.synopsis: Before the Jedi can leave Mortis, Ahsoka Tano is taken captive in an attempt to entice Anakin Skywalker to join the dark side.
episodes.title: Altar of Mortis

episodes.synopsis: The Jedi remain stranded on Mortis, with Anakin Skywalker caught in an epic struggle between the light side and the dark side of the Force.
episodes.title: Ghosts of Mortis

episodes.synopsis: Led by Obi-Wan and Anakin, an elite rescue team attempts to free a captive Jedi general from an impenetrable Separatist prison.
episodes.title: The Citadel

episodes.synopsis: Having freed the prisoners, Obi-Wan Kenobi and Anakin Skywalker search for a way out of the impenetrable Citadel prison.
episodes.title: Counterattack

episodes.synopsis: After their ship destroyed, Anakin Skywalker and Obi-Wan Kenobi must find a new means of escape from The Citadel.
episodes.title: Citadel Rescue

episodes.synopsis: Ahsoka Tano and a group of abducted younglings find themselves stranded on Wasskah, on the run from cruel and deadly Trandoshan hunting parties.
episodes.title: Padawan Lost

episodes.synopsis: As Ahsoka and the younglings struggle to evade the Trandoshan hunters and escape from captivity, their efforts receive an unexpected boost.
episodes.title: Wookiee Hunt

episodes.synopsis: Separatists stir up trouble among the underwater natives of the planet Mon Cala, the Mon Calamari and the Quarren, after their king is assassinated.
episodes.title: Water War

episodes.synopsis: Separatist Riff Tamson launches a surprise attack that scatters the Mon Calamari and their Jedi allies, forcing them to hide in underwater caves.
episodes.title: Gungan Attack

episodes.synopsis: The Republic and Mon Calamari forces have been defeated and captured by Riff Tamson, who seeks to rule Mon Cala as its new king.
episodes.title: Prisoners

episodes.synopsis: When the leader of the Gungans, Boss Lyonie, is injured it's discovered there is an uncanny resemblance between the Boss and Jar Jar Binks.
episodes.title: Shadow Warrior

episodes.synopsis: After quakes devastate the planet Aleen, R2-D2 and C-3PO are sent along to assist as part of a Republic relief mission.
episodes.title: Mercy Mission

episodes.synopsis: After fleeing a battle, C-3PO and R2-D2 embark on a series of bizarre misadventures, like being captured by the tiny denizens of a strange planet.
episodes.title: Nomad Droids

episodes.synopsis: When Anakin is forced to temporarily turn over command of his clone troopers to General Krell, tensions begin to run high.
episodes.title: Darkness on Umbara

episodes.synopsis: General Krell orders Captain Rex and the clone troopers of the 501st Legion to conquer a heavily fortified Umbaran airbase.
episodes.title: The General

episodes.synopsis: After the Republic conquers an Umbaran airbase, General Krell orders Rex and his men towards the heavily fortified enemy capital.
episodes.title: Plan of Dissent

episodes.synopsis: With two of his men facing execution for disobeying orders, Captain Rex must confront his overly aggressive commander, General Krell.
episodes.title: Carnage of Krell

episodes.synopsis: Zygerrian slavers are behind the sudden disappearance of an entire colony of people on the planet Kiros.
episodes.title: Kidnapped

episodes.synopsis: To locate the missing colonists, Anakin, Obi-Wan and Ahsoka go undercover to infiltrate the slavers on Zygerria.
episodes.title: Slaves of the Republic

episodes.synopsis: Anakin tries to convince the Zygerrian Queen that she's a slave and pawn in a Separatist plot. Meanwhile, Obi-Wan toils in the slave camps of Kadavo.
episodes.title: Escape from Kadavo

episodes.synopsis: A peace conference between Separatists and Republic delegates is interrupted by Lux Bonteri, the son of a late Separatist senator.
episodes.title: A Friend in Need

episodes.synopsis: When the Jedi learn of a Separatist plot to kidnap Chancellor Palpatine, Obi-Wan goes deep undercover as a hardened criminal to extract information.
episodes.title: Deception

episodes.synopsis: Fleeing across the galaxy with criminal fugitives, a disguised Obi-Wan, Cad Bane and Moralo Eval are tenaciously pursued by Anakin and Ahsoka.
episodes.title: Friends and Enemies

episodes.synopsis: A disguised Obi-Wan accompanies Cad Bane and Moralo Eval to Serenno, where they join a brutal competition with bounty hunters from around the galaxy.
episodes.title: The Box

episodes.synopsis: The Chancellor travels to Naboo to preside over a public ceremony, guarded by Jedi Knights.
episodes.title: Crisis on Naboo

episodes.synopsis: Count Dooku seeks revenge against the Nightsisters of Dathmoir after their betrayal. Grievous launches a droid attack on the magic-wielding witches.
episodes.title: Massacre

episodes.synopsis: An aimless Asajj Ventress joins a team of bounty hunters under the leadership of young Boba Fett.
episodes.title: Bounty

episodes.synopsis: Dark warrior Savage Opress is on a quest to find his long-lost brother. Could Darth Maul truly be alive, more than a decade after his gruesome death?
episodes.title: Brothers

episodes.synopsis: Savage Opress and Darth Maul pursue Obi-Wan Kenobi for revenge, and the Jedi Knight finds himself forced to unite with a surprising ally.
episodes.title: Revenge

episodes.synopsis: Fueled by rage, newly reunited brothers Savage Opress and Darth Maul spread terror and violence across the galaxy in their quest for vengeance.
episodes.title: Revival

episodes.synopsis: On the Separatist world of Onderon, Anakin, Obi-Wan and Ahsoka train rebels who are plotting to take control of the capital.
episodes.title: A War on Two Fronts

episodes.synopsis: Supervised by Ahsoka, the Onderon rebels infiltrate the capital and execute strikes on targets all over the city. Later, the rebels pick a new leader.
episodes.title: Front Runners

episodes.synopsis: After an unsuccessful rebel attempt to rescue Onderon's true king, an unlikely ally steps forward to halt his execution and aid the rebel cause.
episodes.title: The Soft War

episodes.synopsis: As an all-out revolt embroils Onderon, the rebels strike a decisive blow against the planet's Separatist-aligned king. But victory comes at a cost.
episodes.title: Tipping Points

episodes.synopsis: Ahsoka escorts a group of younglings to Ilum, where they'll undergo a crucial rite of passage: the construction of their light sabers.
episodes.title: The Gathering

episodes.synopsis: As the younglings return from Ilum with Ahsoka, their vessel comes under attack by Hondo's gang of pirates.
episodes.title: A Test of Strength

episodes.synopsis: Using their wits and courage, the younglings work together to rescue Ahsoka from Hondo's pirates.
episodes.title: Bound for Rescue

episodes.synopsis: When Grievous attacks the pirate base on Florrum, Ahsoka and the younglings join forces with Hondo and his pirates to turn back the Separatists.
episodes.title: A Necessary Bond

episodes.synopsis: R2-D2 becomes part of a Republic droid team chosen for an important mission to obtain an encryption module from the Separatists.
episodes.title: Secret Weapons

episodes.synopsis: Col. Gascon, R2-D2 and the other droids crash on a barren planet, where they must cross a bewildering expanse of emptiness to carry out their mission.
episodes.title: A Sunny Day in the Void

episodes.synopsis: Stranded on the planet Abafar, Col. Gascon meets a Republic clone he's determined to free. Meanwhile, the droids must commandeer a Separatist shuttle.
episodes.title: Missing in Action

episodes.synopsis: Col. Gascon and his droid team discover that a seemingly abandoned Jedi cruiser is a death trap headed toward an important Republic conference.
episodes.title: Point of No Return

episodes.synopsis: Realizing they have a common enemy in Jedi general Obi-Wan Kenobi, Savage and Maul forge an alliance with the terrorist group Death Watch.
episodes.title: Eminence

episodes.synopsis: With the backing of the Hutts and an army of the galaxy's most vicious criminals, Pre Vizsla and Darth Maul lead an attack on the planet of Mandalore.
episodes.title: Shades of Reason

episodes.synopsis: Using Duchess Satine as bait, the vengeful Darth Maul lures Obi-Wan into a trap. Drunk with power, Maul declares himself the true Sith Lord.
episodes.title: The Lawless

episodes.synopsis: Anakin and Ahsoka are recalled from the frontlines to investigate a deadly explosion at the Jedi Temple.
episodes.title: Sabotage

episodes.synopsis: When Ahsoka confronts the prime suspect in the Jedi Temple bombing, she suddenly finds herself falsely accused of an unthinkable crime.
episodes.title: The Jedi Who Knew Too Much

episodes.synopsis: While Ahsoka is on the run from the Republic, her search for answers leads to a surprising alliance.
episodes.title: To Catch a Jedi

episodes.synopsis: As Ahsoka is being prosecuted in the high courts for murders she didn't commit, Anakin hunts for the real killer.
episodes.title: The Wrong Jedi

episodes.synopsis: A clone trooper suffers a mysterious mental illness, resulting in the death of a Jedi master and an attack by the Separatists.
episodes.title: The Unknown

episodes.synopsis: While investigating the assassination, ARC trooper Fives uncovers a secret buried in the Kaminoan cloning program.
episodes.title: Conspiracy

episodes.synopsis: Clone cadet Tup is transported back to Coruscant, where his body is to be examined. Fives, meanwhile, conducts his own research.
episodes.title: Fugitive

episodes.synopsis: In an effort to find answers about the assassination, Fives attempts to speak with Chancellor Palpatine personally, only to find himself on the run.
episodes.title: Orders

episodes.synopsis: Padmé Amidala's friend, Rush Clovis, asks her for her help after he becomes the target of a bounty hunter.
episodes.title: An Old Friend

episodes.synopsis: While Clovis is cutting a corrupt deal, his presence strains Anakin and Padmé's relationship to the breaking point.
episodes.title: The Rise of Clovis

episodes.synopsis: Clovis's deal with the Separatists backfires and brings war to Scipio, forcing the Republic to intervene.
episodes.title: Crisis at the Heart

episodes.synopsis: An ancient prophecy threatens the spiritual balance of the planet Bardotta; Jar Jar asks Mace Windu for his guidance on the matter.
episodes.title: The Disappeared: Pt. 1

episodes.synopsis: Jar Jar Binks and Mace Windu must locate a missing queen.
episodes.title: The Disappeared: Pt. II

episodes.synopsis: The Jedi renew their investigation into the disappearance of Sifo-Dyas.
episodes.title: The Lost One

episodes.synopsis: Yoda is troubled after hearing Qui-Gon Jinn's voice from beyond the grave.
episodes.title: Voices

episodes.synopsis: Yoda undergoes training to uncover the secret to immortality.
episodes.title: Destiny

episodes.synopsis: On the ancient Sith world of Moraband, Yoda faces the evil of the Sith.
episodes.title: Sacrifice
